PHASE 3 — CROSS-TOOL STORY RECONSTRUCTION (ECC architect + ECC tdd-guide)
======================================================================

This is the differentiator. When a user asks "what happened with pricing?", Neuron must return ONE connected timeline that stitches the Slack discussion, the Linear decision/ticket, and the Notion summary into a single story — not three separate search results.

Adopt ECC architect methodology to design, then ECC tdd-guide to build.

Design:
- New retrieval mode on top of the existing query pipeline. After the normal vector search returns relevant chunks across ALL sources (Slack, Notion, Linear), group them into a coherent "story":
  - Cluster chunks that refer to the same topic/decision (by embedding similarity + shared entities/keywords)
  - Order them chronologically using each chunk's source timestamp (normalize Slack/Notion/Linear timestamps to a common format)
  - Tag each chunk's role in the story: discussion (Slack), decision/execution (Linear), documentation (Notion)
- Send the ordered, role-tagged chunks to GPT-4o with a prompt that reconstructs the narrative: "Here is what happened, in order, across your tools," with inline citations to each source and a deep link.
- Flag conflicts: if two sources disagree (e.g., Slack says price = $20, Notion doc says $25), surface it explicitly using the existing conflict-detection idea.

Data:
- No heavy new schema needed if chunks already carry source, timestamp, and metadata. Add a lightweight StoryThread concept only if needed to cache reconstructed stories. Prefer computing on the fly first; cache later if slow.

API:
- Extend POST /api/query with a mode (e.g. { mode: "story" }) OR add POST /api/query/story that returns the reconstructed timeline: an ordered array of { source, role, content, author, timestamp, url, labels } plus a synthesized narrative answer and any conflicts.

UI:
- In the query page, when results form a story, render a vertical timeline: each node shows the source icon (Slack/Notion/Linear), the role tag (Discussion / Decision / Summary), the snippet, who said it, when, and a link out. Above it, the synthesized "here's the full story" answer with citations. Use Framer Motion for the timeline reveal (staggered).
- This is the screenshot-able moment — make it clean and obviously magical.

Tests (write FIRST):
- Chunks from 3 sources about one topic cluster into one story
- Story is ordered correctly by true chronology across mixed timestamp formats
- Each chunk gets the right role tag by source
- Single-source query still returns a sensible (degenerate) story
- Conflicting values across sources are flagged
- Visibility respected: personal chunks from other users never appear

